<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND
        RINGS REMOVAL &#38; REASSEMBLY - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>DURING INSTALLATION, INSTALL THE ALUMINUM CONNECTING ROD GUIDE PROTECTOR CAPS ZTSE4153 OVER
                    CONNECTING ROD BOLTS. THIS PREVENTS DAMAGE TO THE CRANKSHAFT JOURNALS. REFER TO THE NOTE BELOW AND
                    FIGURE
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350512">5.12</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The rod bearing inserts must be in place before installing protector caps ZTSE4153.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the crankshaft so the No.1 crankpin is at the bottom of its stroke.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the cylinder bores, crankshaft journals, pistons and piston rings with clean engine
                oil. Install rings using piston ring expander.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12387a" filename="../figcg1/CG12387A.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.12 Connecting Rod Installation Guide and Protector Caps Installed on Connecting Rod
                    Bolts
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Top and intermediate (2nd) rings are to be installed with identification marks facing up.
                        Refer to Figures
                        <hotlnk document="e435_88.xml" xrefid="ef4350503">5.4</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk document="e435_89.xml" xrefid="ef4350505">5.5</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the piston and rod into the piston ring compressor (with ring gaps spaced 120&#176;
                apart). Carefully push down on the piston until it is in the cylinder. Avoid striking the cylinder wall
                and crankshaft (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350513">5.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                Repeat for each rod and piston assembly.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be careful when installing the piston and rod assembly so the crankpin and/or cylinder bore
                        are not damaged.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>THE CONNECTING ROD AND PISTON MUST BE POSITIONED AS FOLLOWS:</para>
                    <seqlist style="arabic">
                        <item>
                            <para>CONNECTING ROD - THE LARGE CHANGER (9, FIGURE
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350514">5.14</hotlnk>) MUST BE LOCATED NEXT TO THE CRANKSHAFT FILLET
                                (4, FIGURE
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350514">5.14</hotlnk>).
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>PISTON - THE ARROW ON TOP OF THE PISTON (FIGURE
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350515">5.15</hotlnk>) MUST FACE CAM SIDE OF THE ENGINE BLOCK.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350513" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11088" filename="../figcg1/CG11088.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.13 Installation of Piston in Cylinder Block</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350514" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10560" filename="../figcg1/CG10560.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.14 Illustrating Proper Installation of Connecting Rod to Crankshaft</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Split in Bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Connecting Rod</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Crankshaft</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Crankshaft Fillet</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Bearing</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Connecting Rod Bearing - Upper</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. Connecting Rod Bearing - Lower</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. Connecting Rod Bearing Cap</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. Large Chamfer Side (Next to Fillet)</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. Small Chamfer Side</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. Piston Bushing Pin</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove connecting rod guide protector caps.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat bearing shell wear surface with clean engine oil and install connecting rod bearings
                and caps.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Rods and caps are matched. Assemble connecting rod and cap with matching identification code
                        on the same crankpin from which removed. Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350516">5.16</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Follow instructions for
                        <hotlnk document="e435_97.xml" xrefid="hl4350502">"Fitting Connecting Rod Bearings"</hotlnk>, in
                        this section, prior to FINAL torque of connecting rod bearing caps.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to clean bolt threads prior to tightening.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use an air wrench when installing connecting rod bolts and nuts. Such practice will
                        cause seizure of the connecting rod bolt or nut threads.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten connecting rod bolts and nuts to specified torque.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat steps 1-7 for the remaining connecting rods and pistons.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recheck connecting rod end clearance using a feeler gauge as outlined under
                <hotlnk document="e435_97.xml" xrefid="hl4350502">"Fitting Connecting Rod Bearings"</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall the following:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Oil Pan</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cylinder Heads w/New Gaskets</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Nozzles w/New Copper Gasket</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil Dipstick</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Exhaust Manifolds</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Valley Pan and Gaskets</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Intake Manifold</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Pump</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Lines</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Glow Plug Harness and Controller</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>Refer to appropriate manual section for detailed assembly instructions.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill engine with specified type and quantity of oil prior to operation.</para>
            <figure id="ef4350515" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12354" filename="../figcg1/CG12354.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.15 7.3L Piston (Top View)</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350516" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10561" filename="../figcg1/CG10561.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.16 Connecting Rod Identification Code (Must be matched prior to assembly)</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
